velinov.java.finken.drone.real

Interface RealFinkenDrone

  • All Superinterfaces:
    EventDispatchable, FinkenDrone, java.lang.Runnable, VrepObject
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    StandardRealFinkenDrone

    public interface RealFinkenDrone
extends FinkenDrone, java.lang.Runnable
    Describes a V-REP model of a real-world finken drone. The V-REP model of a real drone behaves like the real, physical flying quadrocopter. It subscribes to its telemetry messages - ROTORCRAFT_FP and FINKEN_SYSTEM_MODEL and retrieves the live parametars: pitch, yaw, roll, throttle and height from the messages to update the V-REP model with them. The RealFinkenDrone gets updated with the proximity sensor values from the V-REP model and sends them as a SONAR_UPLINK Message on the Ivy-Bus to the real-drone.
    Since:
    May 24, 2015
    Author:
    Vladimir Velinov
